Me_Meth_Desc: A filtered sample is passed through a column containing granulated copper-cadmium to reduce nitrate to nitrite. The nitrite (that originally present plus that reduced to nitrate) is determined by diazotizing with sulfanilamide and coupling with N-(1-naphthyl)-ethylenediamine dihydrochloride to form a highly colored azo dye which is measured colorimetrically.

A filtered sample is passed through a column containing granulated copper-cadmium to reduce nitrate to nitrite. Me_Meth_Desc: A filtered sample is passed through a column containing granulated copper-cadmium to reduce nitrate to nitrite. The nitrite (that originally present plus that reduced to nitrate) is determined by diazotizing with sulfanilamide and coupling with N-(1-naphthyl)-ethylenediamine dihydrochloride to form a highly colored azo dye which is measured colorimetrically.

Me_Meth_Long_Name: Membrane Filter Technique for Members of the Coliform Group: 9222D. Fecal Coliform Membrane Filter Procedure. 9222G. MF Partition Procedures
Me_Meth_Desc: Filter sample through a membrane filter. Place membrane on mFC agar containing aniline blue as indicator. Incubate at 44.5C for 22-24 h. Colonies that are various shades of blue are positive for fecal coliforms. The blue color indicates the capability to ferment lactose to acid. Requirements: ingredients for mFC agar; buffer for rinsing and dilutions; culture dishes (50x10mm); 0.65 micron membrane filters micron membrane filters, certified to fully retain fecal coliforms.Standard Methods, 18th

Me_Meth_Long_Name: Membrane Filter Technique for Members of the Coliform Group: 9222D. Fecal Coliform Membrane Filter Procedure. 9222G. MF Partition Procedures
Me_Meth_Desc: Filter sample through a membrane filter. Place membrane on mFC agar containing aniline blue as indicator. Incubate at 44.5C for 22-24 h. Colonies that are various shades of blue are positive for fecal coliforms. The blue color indicates the capability to ferment lactose to acid. Requirements: ingredients for mFC agar; buffer for rinsing and dilutions; culture dishes (50x10mm); 0.65 micron membrane filters micron membrane filters, certified to fully retain fecal coliforms.Standard Methods, 18th

Me_Meth_Desc: A filtered sample is passed through a column containing granulated copper-cadmium to reduce nitrate to nitrite. The nitrite (that originally present plus that reduced to nitrate) is determined by diazotizing with sulfanilamide and coupling with N-(1-naphthyl)-ethylenediamine dihydrochloride to form a highly colored azo dye which is measured colorimetrically.

Me_Meth_Long_Name: Membrane Filter Technique for Members of the Coliform Group: 9222D. Fecal Coliform Membrane Filter Procedure. 9222G. MF Partition Procedures
Me_Meth_Desc: Filter sample through a membrane filter. Place membrane on mFC agar containing aniline blue as indicator. Incubate at 44.5C for 22-24 h. Colonies that are various shades of blue are positive for fecal coliforms. The blue color indicates the capability to ferment lactose to acid. Requirements: ingredients for mFC agar; buffer for rinsing and dilutions; culture dishes (50x10mm); 0.65 micron membrane filters micron membrane filters, certified to fully retain fecal coliforms.Standard Methods, 18th

Me_Meth_Long_Name: Membrane Filter Technique for Members of the Coliform Group: 9222D. Fecal Coliform Membrane Filter Procedure. 9222G. MF Partition Procedures
Me_Meth_Desc: Filter sample through a membrane filter. Place membrane on mFC agar containing aniline blue as indicator. Incubate at 44.5C for 22-24 h. Colonies that are various shades of blue are positive for fecal coliforms. The blue color indicates the capability to ferment lactose to acid. Requirements: ingredients for mFC agar; buffer for rinsing and dilutions; culture dishes (50x10mm); 0.65 micron membrane filters micron membrane filters, certified to fully retain fecal coliforms.Standard Methods, 18th

A filtered sample is passed through a column containing granulated copper-cadmium to reduce nitrate to nitrite. The nitrite (that originally present plus that reduced to nitrate) is determined by diazotizing with sulfanilamide and coupling with N-(1-naphthyl)-ethylenediamine dihydrochloride to form a highly colored azo dye which is measured colorimetrically.

Me_Meth_Long_Name: Membrane Filter Technique for Members of the Coliform Group: 9222D. Fecal Coliform Membrane Filter Procedure. 9222G. MF Partition Procedures
Me_Meth_Desc: Filter sample through a membrane filter. Place membrane on mFC agar containing aniline blue as indicator. Incubate at 44.5C for 22-24 h. Colonies that are various shades of blue are positive for fecal coliforms. The blue color indicates the capability to ferment lactose to acid. Requirements: ingredients for mFC agar; buffer for rinsing and dilutions; culture dishes (50x10mm); 0.65 micron membrane filters micron membrane filters, certified to fully retain fecal coliforms.Standard Methods, 18th

Me_Meth_Long_Name: Phosphorus, Total (Colorimetric, Automated, Block Digestor AA II)
Me_Meth_Desc: The sample is heated in the presence of sulfuric acid, potassium sulfate, and mercuric sulfate for two and one half hours. The residue is cooled and diluted to 25 mL and placed in autoanalyzer for determination of phosphorus by colorimetry.

Com_Description: Sample held beyond normal holding time, material was analyzed for, but not detected.  Value stored is the limit of detection for the process in use.
Me_Meth_Long_Name: Membrane Filter Technique for Members of the Coliform Group: 9222D. Fecal Coliform Membrane Filter Procedure. 9222G. MF Partition Procedures
Me_Meth_Desc: Filter sample through a membrane filter. Place membrane on mFC agar containing aniline blue as indicator. Incubate at 44.5C for 22-24 h. Colonies that are various shades of blue are positive for fecal coliforms. The blue color indicates the capability to ferment lactose to acid. Requirements: ingredients for mFC agar; buffer for rinsing and dilutions; culture dishes (50x10mm); 0.65 micron membrane filters micron membrane filters, certified to fully retain fecal coliforms.Standard Methods, 18th
Uncensored_Val_Comment: Sample held beyond normal holding time, material was analyzed for, but not detected.  Value stored is the limit of detection for the process in use.
